        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 4:35PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 435 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Oxford, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and damage
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Romeo around 440 PM EDT.
Armada around 500 PM EDT.
Memphis around 520 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Riley Center,
Allenton, Lakeville, Berville, Leonard, Brockway, Lake Orion, and
Auburn Hills.

People attending Armada Fair  should seek safe shelter immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
